cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with the decidability of monadic second-order logic extended with a new quantifier. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another likely category as the paper deals with alternating automata over infinite binary trees. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the construction of an emptiness game. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with automata and their semantics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the decidability and undecidability of certain problems related to alternating automata.
